title: Th
author: Koekubakker
pages:
#- The Friend of Tallahassee.


Being welcomed to a place like this is amazing! There can't be more 'welcomeness' in a place like this! In the next pages I explain you why!
#- Imagine.... 

You spawn in a world without knowing anything about it. You are lost and don't know what to do. And suddenly there was a Romec, asking: 'what are your coördinates?
#- From that moment on I felt welcome to Civcraft! He told me exactly where to go in this open world with danger.

#- After a explaination how to find the nearest train station I started my journey! Luckily I was somehow supplied with resources: Bread torches and tools.
#- After a long walk following the instructions of my guide I found the train station that would lead me to the save lands.
I walked to the right platform to take the first leaving train(minecart).
#- The trainjourney took a lot of my time and energy. It was almost dawn and I wasn't even halfways. I was exausted but knew that giving up on reaching the save lands wasn't an option.
#- Following the instructions of my guide while being close to a collapse was hard to do. The cold breeze through the trainshafts made me shiver. 
#- The guide told me to change train on the next station. Where the train track was was nothing more then just a question mark for both of us. It took hours to find the right platform but eventually I made it.
#- Another long journey by train was ahead. I felt weak, my legs where shaking and sweat dripped down into my lap. Although I was resolute to survive in this bare world.
#- Suddenly the train track changed direction! 'The guide told me about this change of direction' was the first thing that came up in my mind. I was getting closer to my destination, the meeting point! It gave me some hope and a little energy.
#- I knew and I waited and stare into the deep tunnel. It seemed like it was never ending. Just untill I saw a little bright spot all the way in the distance! Just that moment I was sure I made it!
#- My guide gave me some food and offered a help. After I regained strength we walked through the hexagon where he showed me around. We even visited a theatre with some great live music! I had such a wonderfull time there!
#- After we had alot of fun in the hexagon we took a more comfortable train to tellahassee! The trip was tollarable. relative to the train journeys I took in the past few days.
#- Just when we arrived I was feeling home! Romec gave me some supplies to start with! I was allowed to build on his land.
#- After I built my house he showed me around in the city. A great place with a lot of oportunities to work and start out as a newcommer!
#- What I did the next weeks was working for diamonds under healthy circumstances. I chopped wood, gathered sugar canes and vines and even started building a bridge for the community.
It earned me enough to keep myself save in this bare world.
#- One thing I am sure about! That is: without my guide I didn't make it. So to end this story I want to say one thing:

'Thank you Romec'

-Koekubakker- 
#- 